The paper discusses a methodology for mapping research productivity by field, which involves analyzing scientific output indexed in the Web of Science. This suggests that the paper may be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), computational geometry (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and software development (cs.SD).
